From 826281767be92c9d150768bd84f08eb3e8e5b853 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 13:26:42 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] airoha: an7563: store env in raw 'u-boot-env' MTD partition

The AN7563 EVB SPI-NAND uses a pure raw MTD layout with the
Airoha BMT (bad block management) layer underneath; UBI is not
in front of the four boot-side partitions (u-boot, u-boot-env,
art, fip). BMT is transparent from U-Boot's point of view, so
the natural place for the U-Boot environment is the dedicated
"u-boot-env" partition (offset 0x7c000, size 0x4000) on
spi-nand0, which is exactly the layout EN7523 uses upstream.

The original AN7563 import inherited UBI-based env from sister
boards which is wrong for this layout: U-Boot would try to
attach a UBI volume that isn't there.

Switch the AN7563 EVB defconfig to MTD-backed env, matching the
upstream EN7523 pattern:

  -CONFIG_ENV_IS_IN_UBI=y
  -CONFIG_ENV_REDUNDANT=y
  -CONFIG_ENV_UBI_PART="ubi"
  -CONFIG_ENV_UBI_VOLUME="ubootenv"
  -CONFIG_ENV_UBI_VOLUME_REDUND="ubootenv2"
  -CONFIG_ENV_UBI_VID_OFFSET=0
  +CONFIG_ENV_OFFSET=0x7c000
  +CONFIG_ENV_IS_IN_MTD=y
  +CONFIG_ENV_MTD_DEV="spi-nand0"

Redundancy is dropped because the dedicated u-boot-env
partition only holds a single CONFIG_ENV_SIZE=0x4000 (16 KiB)
slot.

UBI command / driver options (CMD_UBI, CMD_UBIFS, MTD_UBI*,
UBI_BLOCK, ...) are intentionally left enabled in the defconfig
so users who want to attach a UBI volume on, say, the 'fip'
partition can still do so manually from the U-Boot prompt.

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
---
 configs/an7563_evb_defconfig | 10 +++-------
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig b/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
index abcd49be..8bf8f8f5 100644
--- a/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
+++ b/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
@@ -7,6 +7,7 @@ CONFIG_TEXT_BASE=0x81E00000
 CONFIG_SYS_MALLOC_F_LEN=0x4000
 CONFIG_NR_DRAM_BANKS=1
 CONFIG_ENV_SIZE=0x4000
+CONFIG_ENV_OFFSET=0x7c000
 CONFIG_DM_GPIO=y
 CONFIG_DEFAULT_DEVICE_TREE="an7563-evb"
 CONFIG_SYS_LOAD_ADDR=0x81800000
@@ -36,8 +37,9 @@ CONFIG_CMD_FS_GENERIC=y
 CONFIG_CMD_MTDPARTS=y
 CONFIG_CMD_LOG=y
 CONFIG_ENV_OVERWRITE=y
-# CONFIG_ENV_IS_IN_MTD is not set
+CONFIG_ENV_IS_IN_MTD=y
 CONFIG_ENV_RELOC_GD_ENV_ADDR=y
+CONFIG_ENV_MTD_DEV="spi-nand0"
 CONFIG_ENV_VARS_UBOOT_RUNTIME_CONFIG=y
 CONFIG_NET_RANDOM_ETHADDR=y
 CONFIG_SYS_RX_ETH_BUFFER=8
@@ -68,12 +70,6 @@ CONFIG_AIROHA_SNFI_SPI=y
 CONFIG_CMD_UBI=y
 # CONFIG_CMD_UBI_RENAME is not set
 CONFIG_CMD_UBIFS=y
-CONFIG_ENV_IS_IN_UBI=y
-CONFIG_ENV_REDUNDANT=y
-CONFIG_ENV_UBI_PART="ubi"
-CONFIG_ENV_UBI_VOLUME="ubootenv"
-CONFIG_ENV_UBI_VOLUME_REDUND="ubootenv2"
-CONFIG_ENV_UBI_VID_OFFSET=0
 CONFIG_MTD_UBI=y
 CONFIG_MTD_UBI_MODULE=y
 CONFIG_MTD_UBI_WL_THRESHOLD=4096
-- 
2.43.0

